President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will be attending the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) Leaders Meeting in the United Kingdom from December 2 to 4, 2019. They will also be attending a reception hosted by Queen Elizabeth II at Buckingham Palace. The President will be meeting with other NATO Heads of State and government to discuss the Alliance's progress on burden-sharing, which includes adding over $100 billion in new defense spending since 2016. He will also emphasize the need for NATO to be prepared for future threats, such as those in cyberspace, critical infrastructure, telecommunications networks, and terrorism.